  47. ‌let init l f =
  48.   if l = 0 then [||] else
  49.   if l < 0 then invalid_arg "Array.init"
  50.   (* See #6575. We could also check for maximum array size, but this depends
  51.      on whether we create a float array or a regular one... *)

  53.    let res = create l (f 0) in
  54.    for i = 1 to pred l do

  174. ‌let fold_left_map f acc input_array =

  177.     let acc, elt = f acc (unsafe_get input_array 0) in

  288. ‌let split x =
  289.   if x = [||] then [||], [||]
  290.   else begin
  291.     let a0, b0 = unsafe_get x 0 in
  292.     let n = length x in
  293.     let a = create n a0 in
  294.     let b = create n b0 in
  295.     for i = 1 to n - 1 do
  296.       let ai, bi = unsafe_get x i in
  297.       unsafe_set a i ai;
  298.       unsafe_set b i bi
  299.     done;
  300.     a, b
  301.   end

  303. let combine a b =
  304.   let na = length a in
  305.   let nb = length b in
  306.   if na <> nb then invalid_arg "Array.combine";
  307.   if na = 0 then [||]
  308.   else begin
  309.     let x = create na (unsafe_get a 0, unsafe_get b 0) in
  310.     for i = 1 to na - 1 do
  311.       unsafe_set x i (unsafe_get a i, unsafe_get b i)
  312.     done;
  313.     x
  314.   end

  316. exception Bottom of int
  317. ‌let sort cmp a =
  318.   let maxson l i =
  319.     let i31 = i+i+i+1 in
  320.     let x = ref i31 in
  321.     if i31+2 < l then begin
  322.       if cmp (get a i31) (get a (i31+1)) < 0 then x := i31+1;
  323.       if cmp (get a !x) (get a (i31+2)) < 0 then x := i31+2;
  324.       !x
  325.     end else
  326.       if i31+1 < l && cmp (get a i31) (get a (i31+1)) < 0
  327.       then i31+1
  328.       else if i31 < l then i31 else raise (Bottom i)
  329.   in
  330. ‌  let rec trickledown l i e =

  332.     if cmp (get a j) e > 0 then begin
  333.       set a i (get a j);
  334.       trickledown l j e;
  335.     end else begin
  336.       set a i e;
  337.     end;
  338.   in
  339. ‌  let trickle l i e = try trickledown l i e with Bottom i -> set a i e in
  340. ‌  let rec bubbledown l i =
  341.     let j = maxson l i in
  342.     set a i (get a j);

  344.   in
  345. ‌  let bubble l i = try bubbledown l i with Bottom i -> i in
  346. ‌  let rec trickleup i e =
  347.     let father = (i - 1) / 3 in
  348.     assert (i <> father);
  349.     if cmp (get a father) e < 0 then begin
  350.       set a i (get a father);
  351.       if father > 0 then trickleup father e else set a 0 e;
  352.     end else begin
  353.       set a i e;
  354.     end;
  355.   in
  356. ‌  let l = length a in
  357.   for i = (l + 1) / 3 - 1 downto 0 do trickle l i (get a i); done;
  358.   for i = l - 1 downto 2 do
  359. ‌    let e = (get a i) in
  360.     set a i (get a 0);
  361.     trickleup (bubble i 0) e;
  362.   done;

  366. ‌let cutoff = 5
  367. ‌let stable_sort cmp a =
  368.   let merge src1ofs src1len src2 src2ofs src2len dst dstofs =
  369.     let src1r = src1ofs + src1len and src2r = src2ofs + src2len in
  370.     let rec loop i1 s1 i2 s2 d =
  371.       if cmp s1 s2 <= 0 then begin
  372.         set dst d s1;
  373.         let i1 = i1 + 1 in
  374.         if i1 < src1r then
  375.           loop i1 (get a i1) i2 s2 (d + 1)
  376.         else
  377.           blit src2 i2 dst (d + 1) (src2r - i2)
  378.       end else begin
  379.         set dst d s2;
  380. ‌        let i2 = i2 + 1 in
  381.         if i2 < src2r then
  382.           loop i1 s1 i2 (get src2 i2) (d + 1)
  383.         else
  384.           blit a i1 dst (d + 1) (src1r - i1)
  385.       end
  386.     in loop src1ofs (get a src1ofs) src2ofs (get src2 src2ofs) dstofs;
  387.   in
  388. ‌  let isortto srcofs dst dstofs len =
  389.     for i = 0 to len - 1 do
  390.       let e = (get a (srcofs + i)) in
  391.       let j = ref (dstofs + i - 1) in
  392.       while (!j >= dstofs && cmp (get dst !j) e > 0) do
  393.         set dst (!j + 1) (get dst !j);
  394.         decr j;
  395.       done;
  396.       set dst (!j + 1) e;
  397.     done;
  398.   in
  399. ‌  let rec sortto srcofs dst dstofs len =
  400.     if len <= cutoff then isortto srcofs dst dstofs len else begin
  401.       let l1 = len / 2 in
  402.       let l2 = len - l1 in
  403.       sortto (srcofs + l1) dst (dstofs + l1) l2;
  404.       sortto srcofs a (srcofs + l2) l1;
  405.       merge (srcofs + l2) l1 dst (dstofs + l1) l2 dst dstofs;
  406.     end;
  407.   in
  408. ‌  let l = length a in
  409.   if l <= cutoff then isortto 0 a 0 l else begin
  410. ‌    let l1 = l / 2 in
  411. ‌    let l2 = l - l1 in
  412. ‌    let t = make l2 (get a 0) in
  413.     sortto l1 t 0 l2;
  414.     sortto 0 a l2 l1;
  415.     merge l2 l1 t 0 l2 a 0;
  416.   end
